risk: low
confidence: medium
resolution: "Story accepted via the pm-xtrd exemplar (PR#587): @unbrained/pm-vcs proves a non-PM domain runs on public SDK primitives alone; primitive-gap inventory complete with every gap shipped, filed (pm-v1yo, pm-um4g, pm-4e12 transaction boundary), or out-of-scope."
expected_result: "A platform developer can model a foreign domain (VCS changesets/refs) using only public pm SDK primitives, with a gap inventory feeding filed or waived SDK items."
actual_result: "packages/pm-vcs ships custom types/fields, schema-owned lifecycle, seven domain commands, reviewed-merge hook, event-sourced history with time travel, durable relationship-event projections, and crash-consistent merge reconciliation — zero private core imports, packed-artifact acceptance at 100% coverage; GAP_REPORT.md dispositions all twelve domain needs."
