  "2026-07-11T10:49:01.607Z",maintainer-agent,"Maintainer re-affirmed 2026-07-11: this story is an explicit product goal (build a git-like VCS or an entire company's business logic on pm SDK primitives alone). Plan of record lives in the SDK-DX map note on epic pm-usfg (2026-07-11) — primitive checklist with owners, and the sequencing rule: the pm-xtrd changeset-exemplar spike runs AFTER the six promotion slices land and is the honest detector of missing primitives; no speculative SDK features ahead of it. Acceptance sketch for this story: the spike's package imports only public SDK entry points (boundary gate pm-8778 proves it), defines its own item types/statuses via the schema primitives, and replays its full event history through the immutable history stream."
  "2026-07-18T10:03:08.216Z",maintainer-agent,"Story acceptance evidence 2026-07-18 (PR#587): exemplar child pm-xtrd CLOSED — @unbrained/pm-vcs models the full changeset/ref domain on public SDK primitives only (custom types+fields, schema-owned lifecycle, seven domain verbs, reviewed-merge hook, event-sourced history with time travel, durable commits_to stream + projections, crash-consistent merge reconciliation). Primitive-gap inventory = packages/pm-vcs/GAP_REPORT.md; every row Complete, explicitly waived (atomic multi-item+relationship transaction boundary — tracked separately under pm-usfg), or out-of-scope (content-addressed storage/tree diff/transport = VCS-product concerns). Gaps surfaced during the lane filed as pm-v1yo (alias collision diagnostics) + pm-um4g (audit unit consistency). All three AC clauses met."
